   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Project 79 \\u2014 Classification Fine-Tune Readiness Audit\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Check whether a dataset is ready for fine-tuning \\u2014 locally.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Component | Choice |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|-----------|--------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| LLM | Ollama (qwen3:8b) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Data | pandas |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Interface | Jupyter |\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 1 \\u00b7 What You Will Learn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Audit **class balance, text quality, label consistency**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Estimate **minimum viable dataset size**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Generate a **readiness scorecard**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 2 \\u00b7 Why It Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Fine-tuning on bad data wastes compute. Catch problems first.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 3 \\u00b7 Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# !pip install -q langchain langchain-ollama pandas\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 4 \\u00b7 Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import json\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"MODEL = 'qwen3:8b'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"llm = ChatOllama(model=MODEL, temperature=0.1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'LLM ready: {MODEL}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 5 \\u00b7 Sample Dataset\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"DATA = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Server 500 error on login', 'label': 'bug'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Add dark mode please', 'label': 'feature_request'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'App crashes uploading large files', 'label': 'bug'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Can you add CSV export?', 'label': 'feature_request'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Great product!', 'label': 'praise'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Dashboard is slow', 'label': 'bug'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Add 2FA', 'label': 'feature_request'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': '', 'label': 'bug'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'asdfghjkl', 'label': 'bug'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Need API integration', 'label': 'feature_request'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Works perfectly!', 'label': 'praise'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Button broken on mobile', 'label': 'bug'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Multi-language support?', 'label': 'feature_request'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'Excellent service', 'label': 'praise'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {'text': 'I want a refund', 'label': 'complaint'},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(DATA)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'{len(df)} entries, {df[\\\"label\\\"].nunique()} classes')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 6 \\u00b7 Check: Stats and Balance\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print('CLASS DISTRIBUTION:', df['label'].value_counts().to_string(), sep='\\\\n')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"counts = df['label'].value_counts()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"imb = counts.max() / counts.min() if counts.min() > 0 else float('inf')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Imbalance ratio: {imb:.1f}x')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['tlen'] = df['text'].str.len()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Empty texts: {df[\\\"text\\\"].str.strip().eq(\\\"\\\").sum()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Avg length: {df[\\\"tlen\\\"].mean():.0f}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 7 \\u00b7 Check: Text Quality\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"issues = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, r in df.iterrows():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    t = r['text'].strip()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if not t: issues.append((i, 'empty'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif len(t) < 5: issues.append((i, 'too_short'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif not any(c.isalpha() for c in t): issues.append((i, 'no_letters'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Issues: {len(issues)}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for idx, issue in issues: print(f'  [{issue}] idx={idx}: \\\"{df.iloc[idx][\\\"text\\\"]}\\\"')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 8 \\u00b7 Check: Label Consistency (LLM)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"chk = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ('system','Does text match label? Labels: {labels}. Return JSON: {\\\"matches\\\": true/false}'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ('human','Text: {text}\\\\nLabel: {label}'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"chk_c = chk | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"label_issues = 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for _, r in df.iterrows():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if not r['text'].strip(): continue\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raw = chk_c.invoke({'text':r['text'],'label':r['label'],'labels':','.join(df['label'].unique())})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        s, e = raw.find('{'), raw.rfind('}') + 1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if s >= 0 and not json.loads(raw[s:e]).get('matches', True): label_issues += 1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except: pass\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Label issues: {label_issues}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 9 \\u00b7 Readiness Scorecard\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"sc = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'sample_size': 'PASS' if len(df)>=50 else 'FAIL' if len(df)<10 else 'WARN',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'balance': 'PASS' if imb<=2 else 'WARN' if imb<=5 else 'FAIL',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'text_quality': 'PASS' if not issues else 'WARN' if len(issues)<=2 else 'FAIL',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'label_consistency': 'PASS' if label_issues==0 else 'WARN' if label_issues<=2 else 'FAIL',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('SCORECARD')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for k,v in sc.items(): print(f'  {k:25s}: {v}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"overall = 'READY' if all(v=='PASS' for v in sc.values()) else 'NOT READY' if any(v=='FAIL' for v in sc.values()) else 'NEEDS WORK'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'\\\\nOVERALL: {overall}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"with open('readiness_report.json','w') as f: json.dump({'scores':sc,'overall':overall},f,indent=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Saved.')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 10 \\u00b7 Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Check size, balance, text quality, label consistency\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- LLM label checking catches annotation errors\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- A scorecard gives clear go/no-go signal\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Audit before training \\u2014 always\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
